As guidance to David Bruce, we sent to him three documents: the action program for British Guiana as transmitted to the President under the Secretary's memorandum of August 30, 1961;For a summary of this paper, see Documents 249 and 250. a telegram containing a letter of instructions for the talks from the Secretary;
                                Document 253. and the telegram to which you refer intended to supplement the Secretary's letter.
                                Document 254. We intended the three documents to be parts of one package. While read in isolation the telegram you mention could be misconstrued, I hope you will agree that read in conjunction with the other two documents it will not mislead David Bruce.
